OL,6,FThe sculptor, Jane Robbins, said the
OL,7,Fidea to bring more women into the
OL,8,Fsculpture was about bringing the past
OL,9,Finto the present.
OL,11,F"I didn't want it to just be a figure
OL,12,Fof somebody from the past because what
OL,13,Fshe did was very current, so the idea
OL,14,Fwas I'd get woman of today in Newport-
OL,15,F and the hands are all clasped,
OL,16,Fsymbolising that Lady Rhondda's work
OL,17,Fwith women and women's right continues.
