OL,6,FShe was the first woman to hold a
OL,7,Fhereditary peerage, but she was never
OL,8,Fallowed to take up her seat.
OL,10,FShe was sent to prison and went on
OL,11,Fhunger strike.
OL,13,FShe even survived the sinking of the
OL,14,FLusitania in 1915, crediting the event
OL,15,Ffor some of her activism.
OL,17,FShe said, "what it did do was to alter
OL,18,Fmy opinion of myself.
